# KNOSSOS:START channel-ignores
# Auto-managed by ari sync — channel directories are regenerated on every sync.
# Each channel also has a provenance-driven .gitignore for per-file precision.
.claude/
.codex/
.gemini/
.mcp.json
.opencode/
# KNOSSOS:END channel-ignores

# KNOSSOS:START infra-ignores
# Auto-managed by ari sync — knossos infrastructure directories.
# Session state, internal framework state, and work product patterns.
**/.sos/*
!**/.sos/land/
!**/.sos/land/**
**/.ledge/*
!**/.ledge/shelf/
!**/.ledge/shelf/**
**/.knossos/
# KNOSSOS:END infra-ignores

# Post-infra-ignores allow-list for canonical .ledge/ work-product directories.
# Placed AFTER the auto-managed infra-ignores block so it survives `ari sync`
# regeneration. Eliminates the silent-add-skip recurrence-vector that cost the
# predecessor 10x-dev sprint ~1000+ lines of design-reference artifacts (per
# .ledge/handoffs/HANDOFF-thermia-to-hygiene-2026-04-27.md §5 Option A; thermia
# procession's reconstruction at P0 was the demonstrated cost). Tracks
# work-product directories by default; ephemeral state remains gitignored.
!**/.ledge/handoffs/
!**/.ledge/handoffs/**
!**/.ledge/decisions/
!**/.ledge/decisions/**
!**/.ledge/reviews/
!**/.ledge/reviews/**
!**/.ledge/specs/
!**/.ledge/specs/**
!**/.ledge/spikes/
!**/.ledge/spikes/**
# Filed as DEFER-FOLLOWUP for upstream knossos template patch: ideally these
# allow-list patterns belong inside the auto-managed infra-ignores block (lines
# 86-96 above) so they propagate to all repos via `ari sync`. The
# post-infra-ignores placement here is a per-repo workaround until the upstream
# template lands the allow-list.

# Scratch / temporary files (PT-00.5 recurrence prevention)
tmp/

# Claude Code local settings — MUST NOT commit (FC2-5 origin — contained Asana PAT at commit 15cffee1)
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/settings.local*

# Mutation testing and property-based testing artifacts
.mutmut-cache
.hypothesis/
